   The programs, DETSIM and TAUSIM generate       11
   and display reactions and decays of particles. 12
   DETSIM displays the response of a detector     13
   to the energy deposited by reaction products.  14
   You may choose the initial and final states    15
   and the momentum of the incoming particle.     16
   Monte Carlo generation of events is started    17
   and stopped with F-6. An output file can be    18
   generated which should be used as input to     19
   reconstruction or analysis programs.           20
   Examples of these are provided.                21
   TAUSIM displays the decay of a short-lived     22
   particle. The decay point and impact parameter 23
   are histogrammed. The lifetime can be varied.  24
   Press <Enter> or Click the Mouse when done.    25

