Resolution
                                                  01
            Resolution                            02
            ----------                            03
 The energy resolution for calorimeters           04
   (Delta E)/E is usually given as                05
       (percent resolution)/sqrt(E)               06
        where E is given in GeV.                  07
 "percent resolution" is the actual resolution    08
    at an energy of 1 GeV                         09
 So, for example, if 10% is given then the        10
  resolution at an energy of 4 GeV is             11
          = 10%/sqrt(4) = 5%                      12
                                                  13
 ----------------------------------------------   14
                                                  15
  The spatial resolution is given in cm           16
                                                  17
  Both the spatial and energy resolution          18
  affect the ability of the detector to           19
  reconstruct the energy and invariant mass       20
  of the system.                                  21
